# Sync layer doctrine

`@mia/sync` rhymes with `@mia/agent`: **runtime owns I/O; core is pure; domain is vocabulary.**

| Kind of code | Put it in |
| --- | --- |
| Types, enums, shapes, branded ids | `domain/` |
| Pure decisions (validate, compile, eligibility, intent, registry logic) | `core/` |
| Preview/execute spine, plan store, disk/DB loaders, host façades, MSSQL runners | `runtime/` |
| Host / sink / tool / pool / registry contracts | `ports/` |
| Agent-facing `create*Tool` factories (one capability per folder) | `tools/` |
| Thin MSSQL pool helpers | `adapters/` |
| Test hosts / fixtures | `test-support/` |

**Do not** resurrect `application/`, `application/core/`, or `application/shell/`.

**Import direction** (enforced by `npm run lint:arch`):

- `domain` → `domain`, `ports` (host type-imports only)
- `core` → `domain`, `ports`, `internal`
- `runtime` → `core`, `domain`, `ports`, `adapters`, `internal`, `tools`
- Outside the package: import `@mia/sync` only

**State:** Runtime / SyncHost owns state. Freeze-window registry is installed at the composition root (`runtime/governance/freeze-windows`); core evaluates with an explicit registry parameter.

**Dependency:** Sync must not depend on `@mia/agent` (structural tool/host compatibility only).

**Flat control flow** (monorepo-wide — `first-principles.mdc`): peer handlers + explicit params/state. Never nest handler functions that `.on` from inside a hot path, or register un-cleared repeating timers. Trivial one-shot `setTimeout(() => …)` is fine. Wire listeners at setup. Enforced by `lint:arch` (`flat-control-flow`).

Full contract: `docs/doctrine.md`.
